                    "text": {
                      "value": "<b>The Arctic’s ice sheet is becoming darker, resulting in a reduction of its “albedo” or its ability to reflect sunlight. Glacial microbiologist and 2016 Rolex Award Laureate, Joseph Cook – who is carrying out pioneering research on the phenomenon – says the top few metres of the Arctic’s ice are like a ‘frozen rainforest’. \n</b>"
