                    },
                    "text": {
                      "value": "“Large areas of the Arctic and Antarctic are now colourful and dark – and dark things heat up in the sun, so those areas melt faster,” Cook explains. “If we can use drones, planes and satellites to see what processes are causing the darkening, then we can start to build a model that can project that darkening into the future. With that knowledge, we can start to think about how to mitigate or how to reduce that risk.”"
